Diagnosis. FEMALE (
Fig. 82
). Black. Mandible with five apical teeth (
Fig. 83
). Clypeus with rounded median lobe, median carina complete. Antennal scrobe carinate over torulus. Frons weakly coriaceous. Vertex almost straight. Pronotal disc with anterior corner acute; median carina strong, extending from anterior carina to posterior series of foveae, wide, paralleled by strong linear depression; transverse anterior carina straight, inner margin toothed; lateral margin acute, but not properly carinate; posterior margin paralleled by series of small foveae. Scutellar pit transverse. Mesopleuron with subtegular groove wide anteriorly; anterior fovea elliptical; upper fovea subrounded, central pit deep; lower fovea narrow, upper margin weakly defined (
Fig. 84
). MALE unknown.
